table asyncio_extra174.asyncio_exception_mro_cross_comparison:
  description: "Cross-comparison of asyncio exception class MRO lengths in asyncioexc174mroxcmp namespace — asyncio.CancelledError.__mro__.__len__()==3 (CancelledError > BaseException > object; shortest chain; inherits from BaseException directly without traversing Exception); asyncio.InvalidStateError.__mro__.__len__()==4 (InvalidStateError > Exception > BaseException > object; inherits from Exception; middle MRO length in this spec); asyncio.TimeoutError.__mro__.__len__()==5 (TimeoutError > OSError > Exception > BaseException > object; IS the builtin TimeoutError; longest chain because OSError inserts an extra level between Exception and TimeoutError); KEY PATTERN: the MRO length encodes the exception hierarchy depth: CancelledError(3) skips Exception entirely (BaseException subclass), InvalidStateError(4) goes through Exception, TimeoutError(5) goes through both OSError and Exception; IMPORTANT: asyncio.TimeoutError's 5-entry MRO reveals it is an OSError subclass — it can be caught by 'except OSError'; asyncio.CancelledError's 3-entry MRO (skipping Exception entirely) means it can only be caught by 'except BaseException' or 'except asyncio.CancelledError' (not 'except Exception'); MRO ORDERING: CancelledError(3) < InvalidStateError(4) < TimeoutError(5); verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: asyncioexc174mroxcmp

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [ce_mro_xchk,   asyncio.CancelledError.__mro__.__len__,      [],  3,  "CancelledError.__mro__.__len__() == 3 (BaseException subclass; shortest exception chain in spec); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [inv_mro_xchk,  asyncio.InvalidStateError.__mro__.__len__,   [],  4,  "InvalidStateError.__mro__.__len__() == 4 (Exception subclass; middle chain length); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [te_mro_xchk,   asyncio.TimeoutError.__mro__.__len__,        [],  5,  "TimeoutError.__mro__.__len__() == 5 (OSError subclass; longest chain; includes OSError level); verified with Python 3.14.3"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Standalone invariants — extra174
